-- China Stocks: GF Securities, Gree Electric, Huadian, Huaneng
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-01-11T08:44:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/china-stocks-gf-securities-gree-electric-huadian-huaneng.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  China  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, fell 9.70 points, or 0.4 percent, to
2,276.05. The  CSI 300 Index  declined 0.5 percent to 2,435.61.  Power producers:  Huaneng Power International Inc. (600011)  (600011
CH), the listed unit of China’s largest power group, fell 1.8
percent to 5.39 yuan.  GD Power Development Co. (600795)  (600795 CH), the
largest electricity producer in northeastern China, lost 1.8
percent to 2.76 yuan. Huadian Power International Corp. (600027
CH), the listed unit of China’s fourth-largest power producer,
slid 1.2 percent to 3.31 yuan.  China’s power-use growth may slow to 8.5 percent this year,
the Xinhua News Agency reported, citing Yu Yanshan, deputy
director of the State Electricity Regulatory Commission.
Electricity consumption slowed to 11.7 percent last year from
14.5 percent in 2010, it said.  GF Securities Co. (000776)  (000776 CH), China’s second-biggest
listed brokerage by market value, fell 1.3 percent to 22.30
yuan. Net income may have dropped 49 percent from a year earlier
to 2.06 billion yuan ($326 million) in 2011 on lower revenue, GF
Securities said in a statement.  Gree Electric Appliances Inc. (000651)  (000651 CH), China’s largest
maker of home air-conditioners, slid 3.5 percent to 17.95 yuan,
the biggest loss since Oct. 20. The company will raise as much
as 3.26 billion yuan selling additional new shares on Jan. 13,
Gree said in a statement.  --Zhang Shidong. Editor: Chan Tien Hin  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
